entry.tran: 令（自己）不自量力；使（自己）因目标过高而失败
entry.def: If you say that someone overreaches themselves, you mean that they fail at something because they are trying to do more than they are able to.

example.ex: He overreached himself and lost much of his fortune...
example.tran: 他的雄心太大，结果损失了自己大部分的财产。

example.ex: The company had overreached itself and made unwise investments...
example.tran: 这家公司不自量力地轻率投资。
